    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>An abundant motif in the art of the central highlands of Mexico since Teotihuacan period, generally consisting of a series of rings formed by two simple concentric circles. In pre-Hispanic palatial architecture, these rings are found in series in the upper zone or frieze of the tecpan façade.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000320/GRI-FloCo</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109721/GRI, FloCo terminology (2019-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Motivo abundante en el arte del altiplano central mexicano desde los tiempos teotihuacanos, que consiste generalmente en una serie de aros formados por dos circulos concétricos simples. En la arquitectura prehispanica palacial, series de estos aros se encuentran en la zona superior o friso de la fachada de los tecpan.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000320/GRI-FloCo</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109721/GRI, FloCo terminology (2019-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tlamantli tlen tlahuel oncah ipan arte antiplano mexicano ipan cahuitl teotihuacanos, tlen quimanextia nochipa aros tlachihualli ica ome tlayohualolli. Ipan arquitectura prehispanica tlen ce palacio, tlen ni tlamantli aros oncah iixco zo iixpan tlen ce tecpan.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Eastern Huasteca Nahuatl</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000320/GRI-FloCo</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
